public abstract class Shape2D
extends java.lang.Object

The Shape2D class is the base class for all two dimensional shapes.

calculateContour

protected abstract void calculateContour(java.util.ArrayList<double[]> outContour,
                                         java.util.ArrayList<double[]> inContour)
Calculates the vertices lying on the shapes contour. Either the contour of the whole shape (outShape) or the contour of a smaller version of the shape (inShape), that is used to apply a border around the shape. If inContour is null only the outer contour will be calculated.

Parameters:
outContour - List storing vertices of the shapes contour.
inContour - List storing vertices of the shapes border.

applyColor

protected void applyColor(java.util.ArrayList<double[]> contour,
                          Color color)
Applies a color to each vertex in a list of vertices.

Parameters:
contour - List of vertices.
color - Color that will be applied to each vertex.

applyTexture

protected void applyTexture(java.util.ArrayList<double[]> contour,
                            TextureCoords tc)
Performs a mapping from object coordinates into texture coordinates. If the second parameter equals null texture coordinates will be set to 0.

Parameters:
contour - List storing vertices.
tc - tImage coordinates of the texture image.
